Sentencas: Cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), comprising porous Pr0.35Nd0.35Sr0.3MnO3-delta (PNSM)/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.95 (SDC) cathode Supports, SDC function layers, YSZ electrolyte membranes and NiO/SDC anode layers, were successfully fabricated via suspensions coating and single-step co-firing process.
Titulo: High-performance cathode-supported SOFCs prepared by a single-step co-firing process

Sentencas: The microstructures of electrolyte membranes were observed with scanning electron microscope (SEM).
Titulo: High-performance cathode-supported SOFCs prepared by a single-step co-firing process

Sentencas: The assembled single cell was electrochemically characterized with humidified hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: High-performance cathode-supported SOFCs prepared by a single-step co-firing process

Sentencas: The open circuit voltage (OCV) of the cell was 1.036 V at 650 degrees C, and the peak power densities were 657, 472, 290 and 166 mWcm(-2) at 800, 750, 700 and 650 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: High-performance cathode-supported SOFCs prepared by a single-step co-firing process

Sentencas: Impedance analysis indicated that the performance of cathode-supported cell was determined essentially by electrode polarization resistance, which suggested that optimizing electrodes was especially important for improving the cell performance.
Titulo: High-performance cathode-supported SOFCs prepared by a single-step co-firing process
